OL,4,Cmarathon participant with motor
OL,5,Cneurone disease
OL,7,FMr Gibson, alongside friends Antony
OL,8,FQuant, 51, and Andy Long, 47, will be
OL,9,Fparticipating in the marathon on April
OL,10,F27 in aid of the organisation.
OL,12,FHe plans to walk across the start line
OL,13,Fand cover the last mile on foot in
OL,14,Forder to show the disease, for which
OL,15,Fthere is no cure, has not beaten him.
OL,17,FOf this decision, Mr Gibson, from
OL,18,FBrentwood in Essex, said: "I am
OL,19,Fblessed to still have my walking
OL,20,Fability.
